name: peptide deformylase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
reaction: formyl-L-methionyl peptide + H2O = formate + methionyl peptide [RN:R05635]
comment: Requires Fe(II). Also requires at least a dipeptide for an efficient rate of reaction. N-terminal L-methionine is a prerequisite for activity but the enzyme has broad specificity at other positions. Differs in substrate specifity from EC 3.5.1.31 (formylmethionine deformylase).
